-snowglobe\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"SessionStart\",\"hookName\":\"SessionStart:clear\",\"command\":\"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/hooks-handlers/session-start.sh\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"014ec034-3032-43a0-aeee-2278cadf3279\",\"toolUseID\":\"014ec034-3032-43a0-aeee-2278cadf3279\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T02:19:48.066Z\",\"uuid\":\"828a0881-8d43-4109-a2a2-3741352e110c\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"828a0881-8d43-4109-a2a2-3741352e110c\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/droid-e2e-ci\",\"sessionId\":\"08582822-ff0b-42a4-941c-4c9252ff6c30\",\"version\":\"2.1.66\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/droid-e2e-ci\",\"slug\":\"optimized-snacking-snowglobe\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Stabilize Droid Interactive E2E Tests\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nDroid interactive E2E tests are **mildly flaky locally** and **fail 100% in CI**. All interactive tests using `StartSession` + tmux are affected:\\n- `TestAttributionOnAgentCommit`\\n- `TestAttributionMultiCommitSameSession`\\n- `TestShadowBranchCleanedAfterAgentCommit`\\n- `TestInteractiveMultiStep`\\n- `TestInteractiveContentOverlapRevertNewFile`\\n\\nThe CI artifact shows: Droid starts, auto-generates a greeting (API works), fires Stop hook, receives the user's prompt (echoed in pane), then **never responds**. Test times out at 90s.\\n\\n## Root Cause Analysis\\n\\nFrom the CI pane capture:\\n```\\n>  Powered by Entire: ...\\n>  --model custom:claude-haiku-4-5-20251001 --skip-permissions-unsafe\\n⛬  I see this is a fresh repo with an initial commit and an .entire/ directory...\\n HOOKS  Stop\\n └─ Script: entire hooks factoryai-droid stop\\n └─ Result : Exit code: 0\\n>  create a file called hello.txt containing 'hello world', then commit it...\\n```\\nDroid responded to its auto-greeting (API works), but after the user prompt was sent, no response ever came.\\n\\n### Primary cause: `CI`/`GITHUB_ACTIONS` env vars not unset\\n\\nGemini explicitly unsets these (`e2e/agents/gemini.go:126-128`):\\n```go\\n// Unset CI and GITHUB_ACTIONS so gemini doesn't force headless mode\\ns, err := NewTmuxSession(name, dir, []string{\\\"CI\\\", \\\"GITHUB_ACTIONS\\\", \\\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY\\\"}, ...)\\n```\\n\\nDroid only unsets `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY` (`e2e/agents/droid.go:183`):\\n```go\\ns, err := NewTmuxSession(name, dir, []string{\\\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY\\\"}, d.Binary(), ...)\\n```\\n\\nIf Droid detects `CI=true` and enters single-turn or restricted mode, it explains exactly the observed behavior: greeting works (first turn), then Droid exits or refuses further input.\\n\\n### Secondary cause: PromptPattern `>` is too ambiguous\\n\\nCompare prompt patterns across agents:\\n| Agent | Pattern | Specificity |\\n|-------|---------|------------|\\n| Claude Code | `❯` | Unique unicode char |\\n| Gemini | `Type your message` | Multi-word phrase |\\n| OpenCode | `(Ask anything\\\\|▣)` | Unique phrases |\\n| **Droid** | **`>`** | **Matches everywhere** |\\n\\n`>` matches Droid informational lines, echoed prompts, and any output containing `>`. This causes false-positive WaitFor matches, especially during the auto-greeting phase.\\n\\n### Tertiary cause: No process liveness detection in WaitFor\\n\\nWhen Droid's process exits (single-turn CI mode, crash), `remain-on-exit` keeps the tmux pane alive. `WaitFor` (`e2e/agents/tmux.go:105-152`) polls for the full 90s against a dead pane that will never change. No early bail-out exists.\\n\\n### Contributing factors\\n- **No dialog handling**: Claude has 5-iteration dialog dismissal, Gemini has 10-iteration. Droid has zero.\\n- **No interactive session retry**: `errScenarioRestart` only covers `RunPrompt`, not `WaitFor` timeouts.\\n- **Auto-greeting timing**: Droid generates greeting + fires Stop before user prompt. First WaitFor may match on greeting `>` before Droid is idle.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Stabilization Approaches\\n\\n### Approach 1: Droid Agent Hardening (Recommended - implement)\\n\\nFix Droid-specific issues mirroring patterns from other agents.\\n\\n**File: `e2e/agents/droid.go`**\\n\\n1. **Unset `CI` and `GITHUB_ACTIONS`** in `StartSession` (copy Gemini pattern):\\n   ```go\\n   s, err := NewTmuxSession(name, dir,\\n       []string{\\\"CI\\\", \\\"GITHUB_ACTIONS\\\", \\\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY\\\"},\\n       d.Binary(), \\\"--model\\\", defaultDroidModel, \\\"--skip-permissions-unsafe\\\")\\n   ```\\n\\n2. **Unset `CI` and `GITHUB_ACTIONS`** in `RunPrompt` too:\\n   ```go\\n   cmd.Env = filterEnv(os.Environ(), \\\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY\\\", \\\"CI\\\", \\\"GITHUB_ACTIONS\\\")\\n   ```\\n\\n3. **Add post-greeting stabilization** in `StartSession`. After initial WaitFor(`>`), wait for the Stop hook to fire (greeting turn to complete), then re-verify readiness:\\n   ```go\\n   // Wait for greeting turn to complete (Stop hook fires)\\n   time.Sleep(2 * time.Second)\\n   s.stableAtSend = \\\"\\\"\\n   ```\\n\\n4. **Improve PromptPattern** if possible. Investigate Droid's actual prompt format to find a more specific regex. If the input prompt line has a distinctive format (e.g. starts at column 0 with `> ` followed by cursor), use that. Otherwise, keep `>` but rely on WaitFor's content-change detection.\\n\\n### Approach 2: WaitFor Process Liveness Detection (Recommended - implement)\\n\\nAdd dead-process detection to `WaitFor` so ALL agents fail fast when process exits.\\n\\n**File: `e2e/agents/tmux.go`**\\n\\n1. **Add `IsPaneDead()` method**:\\n   ```go\\n   func (s *TmuxSession) IsPaneDead() bool {\\n       cmd := exec.Command(\\\"tmux\\\", \\\"display-message\\\", \\\"-t\\\", s.name, \\\"-p\\\", \\\"#{pane_dead}\\\")\\n       out, err := cmd.Output()\\n       if err != nil { return false }\\n       return strings.TrimSpace(string(out)) == \\\"1\\\"\\n   }\\n   ```\\n\\n2. **Check liveness in WaitFor polling loop** - bail immediately when process is dead and pattern doesn't match:\\n   ```go\\n   if s.IsPaneDead() && !re.MatchString(content) {\\n       return content, fmt.Errorf(\\\"process exited while waiting for %q\\\\n--- pane content ---\\\\n%s\\\\n--- end pane content ---\\\", pattern, content)\\n   }\\n   ```\\n\\n3. **Optionally expose via Session interface** for testutil logging:\\n   Add `IsAlive() bool` to Session interface (default true for non-tmux).\\n\\n### Approach 3: Interactive Session Retry (Optional - defer)\\n\\nExtend `errScenarioRestart` to cover interactive WaitFor timeouts when process dies. This adds complexity and masks bugs. Defer unless Approaches 1+2 are insufficient.\\n\\n### Approach 4: PromptPattern Architecture (Optional - defer)\\n\\nSeparate `StartupReadyPattern()` from `ResponseDonePattern()` in the Agent interface. Architecturally clean but a larger refactor. Defer until a second agent needs it.\\n\\n### Approach 5: CI/Timeout Tweaks (Complementary)\\n\\n- Bump `TimeoutMultiplier` from 1.5 to 2.0 as safety margin\\n- Already have `E2E_CONCURRENT_TEST_LIMIT: 1` for Droid in CI\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Implementation Plan\\n\\n### Step 1: Fix `e2e/agents/droid.go` — `StartSession`\\n- Unset `CI`, `GITHUB_ACTIONS` alongside `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY`\\n- Add 2s post-greeting stabilization wait after initial WaitFor\\n- Reset `stableAtSend` properly\\n\\n### Step 2: Fix `e2e/agents/droid.go` — `RunPrompt`\\n- Unset `CI`, `GITHUB_ACTIONS` in the env filtering\\n\\n### Step 3: Add `IsPaneDead()` to `e2e/agents/tmux.go`\\n- Implement using `tmux display-message -t <name> -p \\\"#{pane_dead}\\\"`\\n\\n### Step 4: Integrate liveness check into `WaitFor` in `e2e/agents/tmux.go`\\n- Check `IsPaneDead()` each poll iteration\\n- Return immediately with descriptive error if process dead and pattern not matched\\n\\n### Step 5: Optionally bump `TimeoutMultiplier` in `e2e/agents/droid.go`\\n- Change from 1.5 to 2.0\\n\\n### Step 6: Update `e2e/agents/agent.go` Session interface (optional)\\n- Add `IsAlive() bool` if we want process liveness accessible from testutil\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint` — ensure code compiles and passes linting\\n2. `mise run test` — unit tests pass\\n3. Local test: `mise run test:e2e --agent factoryai-droid TestAttributionOnAgentCommit` — verify the specific failing test passes\\n4. Trigger CI workflow: push to branch and run e2e.yml with `factoryai-droid` matrix entry\\n\\n## Key Files\\n- `e2e/agents/droid.go` — Primary: unset CI vars, stabilization wait\\n- `e2e/agents/tmux.go` — Primary: IsPaneDead, WaitFor liveness check\\n- `e2e/agents/gemini.go:126-128` — Reference for CI env handling\\n- `e2e/agents/claude.go:202-219` — Reference for dialog handling pattern\\n- `e2e/agents/agent.go` — Optional: Session interface extension\\n- `e2e/testutil/repo.go` — Optional: logging improvements\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-wt-droid-e2e-ci/a0b13cf5-a566-48f6-af3d-59dfb2944e27.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"fd67cc9d-33b5-4500-9c90-690791392347\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T02:19:47.641Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Stabilize Droid Interactive E2E Tests\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nDroid interactive E2E tests are **mildly flaky locally** and **fail 100% in CI**. All interactive tests using `StartSession` + tmux are affected:\\n- `TestAttributionOnAgentCommit`\\n- `TestAttributionMultiCommitSameSession`\\n- `TestShadowBranchCleanedAfterAgentCommit`\\n- `TestInteractiveMultiStep`\\n- `TestInteractiveContentOverlapRevertNewFile`\\n\\nThe CI artifact shows: Droid starts, auto-generates a greeting (API works), fires Stop hook, receives the user's prompt (echoed in pane), then **never responds**. Test times out at 90s.\\n\\n## Root Cause Analysis\\n\\nFrom the CI pane capture:\\n```\\n>  Powered by Entire: ...\\n>  --model custom:claude-haiku-4-5-20251001 --skip-permissions-unsafe\\n⛬  I see this is a fresh repo with an