\",\"text\":\"## Summary\\n\\nAll changes implemented and verified:\\n\\n### `e2e/agents/droid.go` (3 changes)\\n1. **`StartSession`** — Unsets `CI` and `GITHUB_ACTIONS` (matching Gemini's pattern) so Droid stays in interactive multi-turn mode instead of exiting after the auto-greeting\\n2. **`StartSession`** — Added 2s post-greeting stabilization wait so the greeting turn + Stop hook complete before we send user prompts\\n3. **`RunPrompt`** — Unsets `CI` and `GITHUB_ACTIONS` in `filterEnv` for non-interactive mode consistency\\n4. **`TimeoutMultiplier`** — Bumped from 1.5 to 2.0 as CI safety margin\\n\\n### `e2e/agents/tmux.go` (2 changes)\\n1. **`IsPaneDead()`** — New method that queries `#{pane_dead}` from tmux to detect when the process has exited while the pane stays alive due to `remain-on-exit`\\n2. **`WaitFor()`** — Integrated liveness check: when the pattern doesn't match and the process is dead, returns immediately with a descriptive error instead of polling for 90s\\n\\n`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\\n**Why the primary fix (CI env vars) is most impactful:** The CI artifact showed Droid processing its auto-greeting (API connectivity confirmed) then going silent. This is the exact behavior you'd see from single-turn mode: process one turn, exit. With `remain-on-exit`, the tmux pane stays visible but the process is dead. Unsetting CI vars should resolve the 100%-fail-in-CI issue.\\n\\n**Why `IsPaneDead` is a force multiplier:** Even with the CI fix, any future agent crash or unexpected exit would still waste 90s polling a dead pane. The liveness check converts these from timeout failures into instant, descriptive failures — useful for all agents, not just Droid.\\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":102,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":76416,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens